            "title": "Mohammed Shami Focuses on Fitness Ahead of T20I Series Against England",
            "image": "https://cricketchampion.co.in/webroot/img/news/2101997204_news.webp",
            "description": "India’s first training session ahead of their T20I series against England, which begins on January 22...",
            "content": [
                "<p>India&rsquo;s first training session ahead of their T20I series against England, which begins on January 22, was centered around fast bowler Mohammed Shami, whose fitness has been a major talking point over the past year. Shami, who has not featured in international cricket since the 2023 ODI World Cup final, was seen bowling with intensity during the practice session at Eden Gardens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Despite recovering from an ankle surgery, Shami had missed out on selection for the Border-Gavaskar Test series due to knee swelling. However, he returned to action on Sunday, bowling for over an hour with his knee strapped. Shami&rsquo;s progress was closely monitored by India&rsquo;s bowling coach Morne Morkel, who ensured that the pacer&rsquo;s fitness was on track for the upcoming matches.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shami started his session by marking a good-length area on the practice pitches. He warmed up with a half run-up for over 20 minutes before transitioning to his full run-up. In the nets, Shami bowled to openers Sanju Samson and Abhishek Sharma, displaying encouraging signs of his fitness. Between his bowling spells, he also worked on short- and long-range catching with fielding coach T Dilip and head coach Gautam Gambhir. Shami concluded his session with a ten-minute spell, bowling at near full tilt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 34-year-old pacer&rsquo;s fitness has been a concern for India for the last 12 months. His inclusion in the upcoming T20I and ODI series against England will help the team assess his readiness for the Champions Trophy, scheduled to start on February 19 in Karachi. India&rsquo;s opening match in the tournament is against Bangladesh on February 20 in Dubai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shami is expected to lead India&rsquo;s pace attack during the five T20Is and three ODIs against England. Jasprit Bumrah, who is also working on his fitness, is likely to return for the third ODI on February 12.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alongside Shami, fast bowler Harshit Rana was also seen at the training session, but Arshdeep Singh was absent. Hardik Pandya was the other prominent player in action, contributing with both bat and ball. Pandya also engaged in power-hitting drills with Rinku Singh and Dhruv Jurel, while Rinku and Tilak Varma faced spin bowlers Varun Chakravarthy, Ravi Bishnoi, and Washington Sundar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The batters were under the guidance of newly appointed batting coach Sitanshu Kotak, ensuring they were well-prepared for the challenges ahead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Shami&rsquo;s return to action and the team focusing on fitness, India looks set for the upcoming series against England as they gear up for the Champions Trophy in February.</p>\r\n"
            ],
            "pub_date": "20 Jan, 2025 | 08:40 AM",
            "news_id": 1630
