            "title": "Rishabh Pant to Lead Lucknow Super Giants in IPL 2025",
            "image": "https://cricketchampion.co.in/webroot/img/news/1157879277_news.webp",
            "description": "Rishabh Pant is set to take over the reins as captain of the Lucknow Super Giants...",
            "content": [
                "<p>Rishabh Pant is set to take over the reins as captain of the Lucknow Super Giants (LSG) ahead of the 2025 IPL season. Pant, who was acquired by LSG for a record INR 27 crore (approximately US$ 3.21 million) during the November 2024 mega auction, becomes the most expensive player in IPL history.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pant&rsquo;s appointment marks a significant change for LSG, who have been in search of a new captain after India wicketkeeper-batter KL Rahul led the franchise for the first three seasons. Under Rahul&#39;s leadership, LSG made the playoffs in both their inaugural seasons (2022 and 2023), but fell short of reaching the final on either occasion. The 2024 season proved to be a disappointing one for the franchise, as they finished seventh on the points table.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This will be Pant&rsquo;s second stint as a captain in the IPL, having previously led Delhi Capitals (DC) from 2021 to 2022. However, his time at DC ended on a somewhat strained note after contract talks broke down, leading Pant to enter the 2024 auction. Despite being part of DC since 2016, Pant opted to move on after DC expressed interest in retaining him but were not fully committed to keeping him as captain.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For LSG, the decision to hand Pant the captaincy was part of their plans to rejuvenate the team following a lackluster 2024 season. Before the auction, LSG had retained five key players: Nicholas Pooran, Ravi Bishnoi, Mayank Yadav, Ayush Badoni, and Mohsin Khan. However, the franchise was keen to find an Indian leader to replace Rahul, with Pant and Shreyas Iyer topping their list of potential candidates. After an intense bidding battle with Sunrisers Hyderabad (SRH), LSG secured Pant by raising their initial bid from INR 20.75 crore to INR 27 crore, eventually outbidding Delhi Capitals, who attempted to use their right-to-match card.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pant, who was a central figure for DC in the IPL, had captained the team from 2021, except during the 2023 season when a life-threatening car accident kept him out of action. His leadership skills and aggressive style of play are expected to benefit LSG as they aim to make a strong comeback in the 2025 season.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pant&rsquo;s leadership will be bolstered by a revamped LSG squad, which includes experienced international players like David Miller, Mitchell Marsh, and Aiden Markram, alongside Indian pacers Akash Deep and Avesh Khan. While Pooran, Marsh, Markram, and Miller were also considered for the captaincy role, Pant&rsquo;s strong presence and experience made him the ideal choice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pant will now work closely with head coach Justin Langer and new team mentor Zaheer Khan. Pant and Langer have previously interacted during the Border-Gavaskar Trophy in Australia, and their partnership will be one to watch in IPL 2025 as they aim to guide LSG to success.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n"
            ],
            "pub_date": "19 Jan, 2025 | 08:23 AM",
            "news_id": 1627
